Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of different heap variants on various inputs, including artificial workloads and workloads generated by running algorithms on real map data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions a discrete event simulator used in recent systems networking research, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the structures using standard, well-known optimizations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
